CRIMEAN-CONGO HEM. FEVER - SOUTH AFRICA: BACKGROUND
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
[see also
Crimean-Congo hem. fever - South Africa (E. Cape) 20000203150359]
Date: Fri 4 Feb 2000
From: Stephen Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on CCHF in South Africa were extracted from
the GIDEON software program:
Year(s) Number reported (fatal)
1981 to 1992 101
1992 9 (0)
1993 4 (0)
1994 4 (0)
1995 5 (1)
1996 19 (1) *
1997 1 (0)
1998 5 (1)
* An outbreak at an ostrich abattoir in Oudtshoorn (Western Cape) in 1996
involved 32 suspected cases (17 confirmed; one fatal). Asymptomatic
infection is common among cattle and sheep.
